Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Flattened handle, moderate curve. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Clay medium pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Philetos. An example in the Benaki collection, Alexandria Museum, is from the same die
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0555)
